snippet: Mr. Trump recovered from a humbling second-place finish in the Iowa caucuses; Mr. Sanders prevailed in a state where he has long held an advantage.
abstract: Donald J Trump and Sen Bernie Sanders win New Hampshire primary, buoyed by voter dissatisfaction and anger at mainstream politics; outcome deals rebuke to political establishment and sets stage for protracted, bruising nomination process.

byline.original: By PATRICK HEALY and JONATHAN MARTIN
byline.contributor: Jess Bidgood contributed reporting from Dover, N.H.

lead_paragraph: Mr. Trump recovered from a humbling second-place finish in the Iowa caucuses; Mr. Sanders prevailed in a state where he has long held an advantage.

headline.main: Donald Trump and Bernie Sanders Win in New Hampshire Primary
headline.print_headline: Trump and Sanders Win Resoundingly in New Hampshire
